The Policemen have arrested six persons found with poisonous cow skins (Ponmo). In a statement yesterday, Lagos Command spokeman Bala Elkana, a Deputy Superintendent of Police (DSP), said the suspects were arrested following a tip-off. They are Adelowo Yinka, 50, Olawunmi Onabanjo, 40, Omowami Wasiu, 43, Adeshokan Taiwo, 43, Iyabo Oluwa, 38 and Taye Kazeem, 40. Elkana said: “On May 5, at about 5am, acting on the strength of information from a source that a truck load of cow skins, popularly called Ponmo, suspected to be poisonous, were stored in a warehouse at 9, College Road, Igando, a team of officers led by the Divisional Police Officer, Igando, mobilised to the scene. “The huge pillage and pyramid of poisonous Ponmo and the chemicals used in the preservation of the cow skins, were recovered. “One TATA truck with number plate AKD-375-XB, which was used in conveying the goods, was impounded. “Officials of the Lagos State Ministry of Health were contacted and after examination, the cow skins were confirmed to be poisonous and not fit for human consumption.” Elkana said the command would also protect lives and property. The command, he added,  would ensure the preservation of public health and safety, as enshrined in the constitution. “Investigation is on to ascertain the source and destinations of the poisonous food items. The suspects will be arraigned,” he said.